int for your own situation.  When people realized this they started flaming you.<br><br>Personally, I started making jokes on it, because it became so huge it was getting ridiculous.<br><br>Sure, this is R and R, but I suggest you re-read some of the threads and try and get a feel for what is considered a decent thread.  My favorite of the week is the Drivers Rant.  No one gets too personal but there is a little give and take in the flamage department and people get a little heated.  But it was never intended to bring out a personal dispute between two people and then turned into a plea to get the citizens of this community to take sides.<br><br>People don't like that.  Understand that and accept it.  Problems like that can't be solved here and people tend to get pissed when they are subjected to that kind of play on their emotions.  Wasn't that obvious when even normally laid back people started flaming you on that thread?<br><br>Bjarki <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utarotoflanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarotofLanys</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.nyanna.f2s.com/icons10/butterfly1b.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Moderator Pirate</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/6/02 2:29:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1663.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.gloryroad.net/~arathorn/butterfly.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is Rants and Raves mearly a flame fest?</span><hr size=1> From what I've seen, people don't have so much a problem with the fact that you're a transsexual, as they do with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> specifically.<br><br>Do I give a shit that you're transsexual? Nope. However you've come on the boards, on more than one occasion wielding your life history and personal problems like a club, attempting to bash people into some sympathy.<br><br>Let's go back to the first time, and since I don't know you in game I'm refering only to the boards. You posted that while you were under in patient psychatric care for suicidal idealation someone removed you from a guild. You hammered home the point repeatedly that you were sick. Frankly the details of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> why</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you were offline were inconsequental to the incident. You came off then like a drama queen. LOOK AT ME! LOOK WHAT THEY DID TO ME! POOR ME!<br><br>The people in your guild, some pretty respected people who I know came out and said, look there were a variety of reasons that we're not gonna get into on the boards. You were removed for valid reasons. Let it go. Even if they hadn't logged into your account and /guild removed you, they could have simply done it the next time they caught you logged in. You edited your posts and let it die, because IMO you weren't winning <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> sympathy.<br><br>Then came the now infamous transsexual thread. Again, based on what I heard <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> from Taladan and co, and not from you, but from third parties who felt for some reason I should know all the details as a moderator...which frankly I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> didn't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want to know...that issue had little to do with you being a transsexual and EVERYTHING to do with your actions. <br><br>Your post was not to 'bring to light the tragedy of the transsexuals' though personally I have no doubt that you've deluded yourself into thinking that. It was more drama. It was more 'poor me'. <br><br>We all have our little crosses to bear. Somewhere out there people HATE us. Whether it's because we're Americans, or because we're gay, or because we're black, or because of religious beliefs, there's someone out there willing to kill us for it. And yes, for some people intolerance is much more a daily facet of their lives than others.<br><br>However the problems that people have had with you are with YOU. Not with the labeling. Have some of those people immaturely and shittly used that to slam you? Sure, I'm sure they have. But the issues that most of the people have with you that they haven't aired are because they don't like YOU. Not because you're a transsexual, but because of some things you've done.<br><br>I wouldn't like you if I knew you. Not because I have an issue with transsexuals, I really don't. But because you're someone who whores out personal problems for pity and sympathy. Because you're someone that rather then looking at <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> yourself</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as the problem, and your actions as the problem...finds it so much easier to wallow in self pity.<br><br>I'm going to make another suggestion since you've made all this public. Try taking personal responsibility for your actions. Some of the things you did were pretty fucked up based on some logs I saw. Frankly I think it's pretty sick, especially considering you were screaming about sexual harassment. What you did to at least one other person isn't even borderline in that area. Try taking a good look in that proverbial mirror. <br><br>The problem isn't that you're a woman trapped in a man's body. The problem isn't that you want to have sexual reassignment surgery. The problem isn't that you're gay. You've managed to become involved in one of the few communities in life where <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> what</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you are, and what you look like, and who you fuck really don't matter. People can't see that, they can see the essense of what is you. Or what you choose to project as you.<br><br>That was what people had a problem with. YOU.<br><br>Whether you decide to take that information and make positive changes is up to you. I have no doubt it's more comfortable to think, &quot;Gee people have a problem with me because I'm <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>insert your favorite minority group here</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->. Then it's not about you, it's about things that you can't change. It's not personal. It's not about who you really are.<br><br>But it is...really...about you. And fortunately that's something you can make changes to without surgery. That's something you can look at and change. <br><br>And the positive thing here is that most of the people who had an issue with you were not judging you on being transsexual. They were looking at you. Which is, what you've said you've wanted. <br><br>The majority of these people on Lanys boards don't look at my posts and think &quot;Oh Tarot's a woman&quot; or Rugen's posts and think &quot;Oh, he's gay&quot;, or Surcum's posts and think &quot;Gee, he's black&quot; or Jellah's posts and think &quot;Gee she's the mother of a bi-racial child&quot; etc. These facts of life may come up in posts, though generally they don't. People who don't like me don't like <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> me</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. A few may have issues with me being a moderator, but for the most part people who don't like me, simply just don't like how I am. They may use the fact that I'm a moderator to slam me, but the reality is they simply don't like me.<br><br>And frankly, that's fine. I like me, and I'm happy with who I am. And I have many people in my life that do like me. I have faults, and I know those faults and I try to work on them. That's part of life.<br><br>However when people slam me on the boards, I don't automatically scream that it's 'cause I'm a moderator. Or a woman, or whatever other labels I can attach to myself. It's generally because they don't like something I've said, or done. They disagree with that. And even that's not too personal to me. Probably because for the most part I'm pretty happy with who I am.<br><br>Anyway before this gets to be too long (too late) I'm basically offering you the suggestion that in this rare medium, most people don't give a damn that you're a transsexual. Even those that do have a problem with it don't tend to take it out on people who post, or people who play in game. There are people in these forums that believe in their heart of hearts that homosexuality is fundementally wrong and evil, that can agree with people who are openly gay on the forum on other issues, and aren't dogging their steps on the board or ingame.<br><br>The few people who decide to openly harass others for the most part are pretty much jumped on by everyone else for being such a closeminded bigot. No one cares if someone thinks homosexuality is evil, so long as they're not clubbing others with their beliefs. And that goes both ways.<br><br>People have been telling you since you started posting this kind of crap beginning (I think) w/ the guild removal thread that they have a problem with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and your actions. Not any of the other baggage or details or labels. <br><br>Take it for what it's worth.  <p><a href="http://www.anarchyboard.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://users.gloryroad.net/~arathorn/Tarotsign.jpg" border="0"></a> <br><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Realm </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>RETIRED</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Everquest: Fennin Ro, Karana, Ero Marr & Lanys T'Vyl </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>RETIRED</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Ultima Online: Catskills </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>INACTIVE</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Anarchy Online: Beta Tester, Rubi-Ka 1 </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>RETIRED</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Dark Age of Camelot: Beta Tester;Merlin Midgard</FONT><FONT COLOR=008000 SIZE=1> CURRENT</FONT></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table bord